## EXECUTION WAVE DETAILS

### Wave 1 Execution (Parallel - ~10 mins)
[Execute [1.1], [1.2], [1.3] simultaneously in separate browser/code sessions]

**[1.1] Server Startup Test**
- Start: npm run dev
- Expected: "listening on port 3000" in console
- Verify: curl http://localhost:3000 returns HTML

**[1.2] Database Schema Test**
- Open SQLite: sqlite3 /config/workspace/moonlanding/data/app.db
- Run: PRAGMA table_list;
- Verify: >= 100 tables, includes users, engagements, rfis, reviews
- Check foreign_keys: PRAGMA foreign_keys;

**[1.3] Config Load Test**
- Execute config engine
- Verify: master-config.yml loads without errors
- Check: entities array contains > 10 entity definitions

### Wave 2 Execution (After Wave 1 - ~15 mins)
[Execute [2.1], [2.2], [2.3] in sequence or parallel]

**[2.1] Client Load Test**
- Navigate to http://localhost:3000 in browser automation
- Verify: page loads, no 500 errors, HTML contains login form
- Check: no console errors in browser DevTools

**[2.2] Auth Endpoints Test**
- Test POST /api/auth/login with valid/invalid credentials
- Verify: valid returns 200 + JWT or session cookie
- Verify: invalid returns 401

**[2.3] Health Check Test**
- GET /api/health
- Verify: 200 response, JSON with uptime, db status, app version

### Wave 3 Execution (After Wave 2 - ~20 mins)
[Execute [3.1] → [3.2] → [3.3] → [3.4] → [3.5]]

**[3.1] Login Form Test**
- DOM query: find input[type=email], input[type=password], button[type=submit]
- Interaction: type email, type password, click submit
- Verify: form sends POST to /api/auth/login

**[3.2] Navigation Test**
- DOM query: find buttons with data-navigate attribute
- Click each navigation button
- Verify: URL changes, new page content loads, no errors

**[3.3] Dialog Test**
- DOM query: find buttons with data-dialog-* attributes
- Click to open: dialog should be visible
- Click to close: dialog should be hidden
- Verify: CSS transitions work, overlay present

**[3.4] Event Delegation Test**
- Check window.__events exists
- Register test handler: window.__events.register('test', callback)
- Trigger via DOM: <button data-action="test" data-params='{"id":"123"}'>
- Verify: callback fires with correct params

**[3.5] Form Submission Test**
- Fill form with sample data
- Submit form
- Verify: POST sent, network tab shows request data, response received

### Wave 4 Execution (After Wave 3 - ~30 mins)
[Execute [4.1], [4.2], [4.3]]

**[4.1] E2E Auth Flow**
- Login with test user (or create new)
- Verify: redirect to /dashboard
- Check: user profile visible, greeting shows name
- Logout: verify session cleared, redirect to /login

**[4.2] CRUD Operations**
- Create: POST /api/entity/engagement with test data
- Verify: 201 response, record in database
- Read: GET /api/entity/engagement/:id
- Verify: 200 response, data matches created record
- Update: PUT /api/entity/engagement/:id with changes
- Verify: 200 response, changes persisted in DB
- Delete: DELETE /api/entity/engagement/:id
- Verify: 200 response, record removed from DB

**[4.3] File Upload**
- Prepare multipart/form-data with file
- POST to /api/friday/upload/engagement-letter
- Verify: 200 response, file saved to disk, file ID returned
- Check: file exists at expected path

### Wave 5 Execution (After Wave 4 - ~20 mins)
[Execute [5.1], [5.2], [5.3], [5.4]]

**[5.1] Migration Phase 3.5 Readiness**
- Check file exists: /config/workspace/moonlanding/execute-phase-3.5-real.js
- Parse file: verify no syntax errors
- Check functions: verify orchestrator, validators, transformers present
- Status: ready or needs fixes

**[5.2] Validator Tests**
- Run: RowCount validator on sample data
- Run: RefIntegrity validator (should find 0 orphans in clean DB)
- Run: DataType validator
- Run: Timestamp validator
- Verify: all pass or document failures

**[5.3] Full Integration**
- Create engagement via UI
- Verify visible in API response
- Verify in database query
- Create RFI under engagement
- Verify chain in API and DB

**[5.4] Error Handling**
- Test invalid form data → expect 400 with error message
- Test missing auth → expect 401
- Test DB access during concurrent writes → expect recovery
- Verify: system stays responsive, logs errors, provides feedback

